  "body": "*Description*:\r\n\r\nThis is a follow-up discussion of https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/issues/4548 and https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/pull/4575.\r\n\r\nFrom @snowp in https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/issues/4548#issuecomment-426495302: I think we might want to follow up with figuring out how to reconcile the differences in behavior between STRICT_DNS and EDS, either by getting rid of the differences or acknowledging that they'll be different and making that clearer in code. For instance, EDS guarantees that a host only exists in one priority and will reuse the host instance (and consequently HC status etc.) when a host moves between priorities. Neither of these is true for STRICT_DNS AFAIK.\r\n",
